    <scopecontent id="aspace_4802afbb3ff40e6a8cafb2c018898dc0">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>These tapes feature interviews with rank and file porters in New York, Chicago, Denver and Los Angeles. Interviewees discuss their family background, their emigration north, and their experiences working for the Pullman Company which sometimes dated to the 1910's. The interviews shed light on early race relations in the labor movement, segregation within the AFL, and civil rights in general.</p>
      <p>Index available in repository.</p>
    </scopecontent>
